## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1: DB Schema — `src/shared/lib/db.ts`

Add two entries to the existing `migrations` array (do NOT touch the `CREATE TABLE` block — existing installs use ALTER TABLE for new columns):

```typescript
"ALTER TABLE quotes ADD COLUMN raw_content TEXT",
"ALTER TABLE quotes ADD COLUMN generated_component TEXT",
```

These go at the end of the array. The try/catch loop already handles "column already exists" errors.

### Step 2: Extend the `Quote` Type — `src/features/quotes/types/index.ts`

Extend the `QuoteType` union and the `Quote` interface:

```typescript
export type QuoteType = "line-items" | "blueprint" | "ai-generated";

export interface Quote {
  // ... all existing fields unchanged ...
  // New AI-generated fields
  rawContent?: string;
  generatedComponent?: string;
}
```

No changes needed to `CURRENCY_SYMBOLS`, `CURRENCY_LABELS`, or the calculation helpers.

### Step 3: Extend Queries — `src/features/quotes/lib/queries.ts`

Two changes:

**3a. Extend `rowToQuote()`** — add at the end of the returned object:
```typescript
rawContent: (row.raw_content as string) || undefined,
generatedComponent: (row.generated_component as string) || undefined,
```

**3b. Add `createAiQuote()` function** — a new focused function for the generation pipeline (the existing `createQuote()` is tied to `QuoteFormData` from Zod which doesn't have the new fields and would require a schema change that risks the admin form):

```typescript
export interface AiQuoteInput {
  clientName: string;
  clientEmail: string;
  clientCompany: string;
  title: string;
  currency: Quote["currency"];
  locale: Quote["locale"];
  validUntil: string;
  rawContent: string;
  generatedComponent: string;
  status?: Quote["status"];
}

export async function createAiQuote(data: AiQuoteInput): Promise<Quote> {
  const db = await ensureDb();
  const id = nanoid(10);
  const now = new Date().toISOString();

  await db.execute({
    sql: `INSERT INTO quotes (
            id, client_name, client_email, client_company, title,
            quote_type, currency, locale, valid_until,
            raw_content, generated_component,
            status, line_items, created_at, updated_at
          ) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, 'ai-generated', ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, '[]', ?, ?)`,
    args: [
      id,
      data.clientName, data.clientEmail, data.clientCompany, data.title,
      data.currency, data.locale, data.validUntil,
      data.rawContent, data.generatedComponent,
      data.status ?? "draft",
      now, now,
    ],
  });

  return (await getQuoteById(id))!;
}
```

### Step 4: Registry File — `src/generated-quotes/registry.ts`

This file starts empty and gets updated by the generation pipeline. It must always be valid TypeScript even when empty:

```typescript
